                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">This multitasking exfoliating cleanser uses both chemical and enzymatic exfoliation for a balanced, effective approach: <br><br> • <b>The AHA Dynamic Duo (Glycolic Acid &amp; Lactic Acid):</b> These alpha hydroxy acids work on the skin’s surface to dissolve the bonds holding dead skin together. Glycolic acid helps refine texture and support healthy-looking cell turnover, while lactic acid gently exfoliates and helps hydrate at the same time. The result? A smoother, more radiant-looking face without the harsh feel of a traditional scrub. <br><br> • <b>Fruit Enzymes (Papaya, Pineapple &amp; Pumpkin):</b> These natural enzymes help break down dead skin cells for an immediate smooth-skin effect. They provide enzymatic exfoliation without rough particles or microbeads, so you get polish, not irritation. <br><br> Together, this advanced formula helps deep clean pores, refresh dull skin, and leave your complexion looking healthy and revitalized.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="accordion-item" js-accordion-item="" data-faq-index="2">
                  <button class="accordion-header faq-header w-full items-center flex justify-between pt-20 pb-10 text-left gap-14  hover:!text-black" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion--2" js-accordion-header="">
                    How is this different from other exfoliating cleansers?
                  </button>
                  <div id="accordion--2" class="accordion-content w-full border-b border-gray" js-accordion-content="">
                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">Most exfoliating washes rely on gritty scrubs or harsh particles that can feel rough on the face. This daily exfoliating cleanser takes a more sophisticated approach. Instead of pumice, microbeads, or abrasive scrub particles, it uses a combination of acids and fruit enzymes to exfoliate chemically and enzymatically. The creamy, sulfate-free foam feels cushiony, not scratchy, and leaves skin feeling clean, polished, and invigorated. It’s high-performance exfoliation without compromising comfort, gentle enough for daily use for most skin types.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="accordion-item" js-accordion-item="" data-faq-index="3">
                  <button class="accordion-header faq-header w-full items-center flex justify-between pt-20 pb-10 text-left gap-14  hover:!text-black" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion--3" js-accordion-header="">
                    How often should this product be used?
                  </button>
                  <div id="accordion--3" class="accordion-content w-full border-b border-gray" js-accordion-content="">
                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">This exfoliating face wash is gentle enough for daily use, morning and night. If you prefer a “less is more” philosophy, using it in your evening routine is a great way to exfoliate away dry skin and prep for serums and treatments. As with any exfoliating cleanser, consistency matters more than intensity.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="accordion-item" js-accordion-item="" data-faq-index="4">
                  <button class="accordion-header faq-header w-full items-center flex justify-between pt-20 pb-10 text-left gap-14  hover:!text-black" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion--4" js-accordion-header="">
                    Will exfoliating cleansers increase skin sensitivity?
                  </button>
                  <div id="accordion--4" class="accordion-content w-full border-b border-gray" js-accordion-content="">
                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">Any product that helps exfoliate can increase sensitivity, especially to the sun, because you’re revealing fresher, newer skin underneath. This formula is balanced for daily use, but it’s important to avoid skipping sunscreen during the day. Daily SPF helps protect your smooth, refreshed skin and maintain healthy results. If you’re new to acids, start slowly and monitor how your skin responds.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="accordion-item" js-accordion-item="" data-faq-index="5">
                  <button class="accordion-header faq-header w-full items-center flex justify-between pt-20 pb-10 text-left gap-14  hover:!text-black" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion--5" js-accordion-header="">
                    Can this cleanser remove makeup and SPF effectively?
                  </button>
                  <div id="accordion--5" class="accordion-content w-full border-b border-gray" js-accordion-content="">
                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">Yes, this exfoliating facial cleanser is a true multitasker. It helps remove daily buildup, long-wear makeup, excess oil, and stubborn SPF while cleansing deep into pores. After rinsing, skin feels thoroughly clean and refreshed, rather than stripped. For heavy, waterproof eye makeup, you may still want a dedicated remover first. Otherwise, this exfoliating face wash handles most of the workload beautifully.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="accordion-item" js-accordion-item="" data-faq-index="6">
                  <button class="accordion-header faq-header w-full items-center flex justify-between pt-20 pb-10 text-left gap-14  hover:!text-black" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion--6" js-accordion-header="">
                    Is this suitable for all skin types?
                  </button>
                  <div id="accordion--6" class="accordion-content w-full border-b border-gray" js-accordion-content="">
                      <div class="rte p2 text-charcoal text-12 desktop:text-14 pb-28">Generally, yes. It’s the "Goldilocks" of cleansers. <br><br> • <b>Oily/Combination:</b> It’s a dream for keeping pores clear. <br> • <b>Dull/Mature:</b> It’s essential for speeding up cell turnover. <br> • <b>Sensitive:</b> While it's gentler than most, if you’re extremely reactive, I’d suggest starting every other day to let your skin get used to the AHAs. <br><br> No matter your skin type, this exfoliating cleanser is designed to leave skin feeling polished, refreshed, and healthy, not tight or overworked.</div>
                  </div>
